The paper deals with interference management in wireless networks, which is a common topic in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) communities. The use of coordinated multi-point (CoMP) schemes is also a key technology for next-generation mobile communication systems, which falls under the systems and control (cs.SY) category. The paper also discusses practical issues such as limited backhaul, which is a common concern in multimedia (cs.MM) and communication (cs.COM) systems.
